The paper deals with the detection of malware campaigns using domain generation algorithms, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). The proposed solution involves the use of probabilistic methods, which suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of filters and validation techniques, which could be related to network security (cs.NI) and software engineering (cs.SE).
